text.paragraph:
If there are signs of infection, specimens for cultures should be obtained for the identification of the causative organism so that appropriate therapy may be instituted (see 
                        DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                     ).

When Cefazolin for Injection is administered to patients with low urinary output because of impaired renal function, lower daily dosage is required (see 
                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                           ).

As with other β-lactam antibiotics, seizures may occur if inappropriately high doses are administered to patients with impaired renal function (see 
                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                           ).

Gastrointestinal: Diarrhea, oral candidiasis (oral thrush), vomiting, nausea, stomach cramps, anorexia and pseudomembranous colitis. Onset of pseudomembranous colitis symptoms may occur during or after antibiotic treatment (see 
   WARNINGS
). Nausea and vomiting have been reported rarely.
